AU  - M. She
AU  - Y. Zhao
T2  - 2024 5th International Conference on Electronics and Sustainable Communication Systems (ICESC)
AB  - Digital Twin technology has emerged as a critical tool in various fields, integrating multidisciplinary data to construct virtual models that reflect physical entities throughout their life cycle. This study explores the application of digital twin technology in the context of intelligent fire protection systems, emphasizing the need for a systematic design approach to ensure compatibility, stability, and efficiency. Through a comprehensive examination of hardware-software integration, data processing, fault tolerance, and real-time monitoring, this study outlines a systematic approach to the design of intelligent fire protection systems. Furthermore, the implementation of a digital twin scene and multi-terminal collaboration is elucidated, highlighting the five-dimensional structural model and the role of virtual space. The proposed system is subjected to simulation and systematic verification, demonstrating its effectiveness in real-time data collection, modeling performance, and decision support. This research provides valuable insights into the systematic design and implementation of intelligent fire protection systems using digital twin technology.
