TY  - CONF
TI  - Optimization of Port Logistics performance through Innovative Technology Management
AU  - O. El Imrani
T2  - 2024 IEEE 15th International Colloquium on Logistics and Supply Chain Management (LOGISTIQUA)
AB  - The field of port logistics, which is continually changing, is now heavily impacted by technology advancements. This essay seeks to examine the many aspects of the digital revolution and emphasize the potential it has for organizations to enhance their operational efficiency. We will examine the advancements that are revolutionizing the daily operations of ports, including meticulous container management, the use of real-time traceability technologies, and the incorporation of automated procedures. Container management is the fundamental aspect of contemporary port logistics. Recent technological advancements enable more sophisticated and effective administration of these crucial components. IoT sensors enable sophisticated tracking systems that provide immediate and accurate information on the whereabouts and condition of containers, therefore minimizing the likelihood of loss, damage, or delay. Through a thorough analysis of these advancements, we can ascertain how proactive container management might enhance the strategic organization of port operations. Real-time traceability is an important aspect of technical advancement in port logistics. Businesses may now use sophisticated monitoring and data management systems to monitor and record every stage of the products' journey, starting with their arrival at the port until they reach their ultimate destination. Enhanced transparency not only improves the efficiency of operations, but also instills consumer trust by delivering precise information about their shipments. Process automation is becoming a crucial foundation of technology administration at ports. Automated machinery, such as self-operating port cranes and automated guided vehicles, decrease waiting periods, enhance efficiency, and limit human mistakes. Through the examination of these automated solutions, we will emphasize the notable advantages they provide in terms of operational efficiency and profitability. This essay will examine the dynamic field of port logistics, investigating the technology advancements that are revolutionizing organizations' management of their operations. Through an exploration of container management, real-time traceability, and process automation, we want to emphasize the latest trends and most effective methods that will drive the industry towards enhanced performance.
