TI  - Resource Optimization Method for Industrial Internet of Things Based on Deep Reinforcement Learning
AU  - J. Li
T2  - 2025 5th International Conference on Artificial Intelligence and Industrial Technology Applications (AIITA)
AB  - The effective deployment of the Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) in the framework of the fourth industrial revolution and automated manufacturing depends on the cooperation of numerous effective and networked devices, and the Digital Twin can monitor and analyze the status of equipment in real-time, predict failures, and optimize production distances by building virtual copies of physical objects, enabling the Industrial IoT to achieve efficient network services and flexible network management. However, the dynamic changes of the IIoT environment, limited spectrum resources, and the requirements of low latency, low energy consumption, and high security of IIoT devices have brought great challenges to the practical application of IIoT. this paper studies the resource allocation problem in the IIoT environment and proposes a resource optimization for short packet communication (SPC) under the constraint of security capacity based on the deep reinforcement learning method. Considering the constraints of minimum security capacity and total bandwidth, the total power minimization problem of the short packet secure communication under the IIoT is constructed. According to the optimization objectives and constraints, a dual-depth Q network for bandwidth resource decision-making and a power resource optimization network based on deep deterministic policy gradient were designed. The simulation results show that the intelligent resource optimization algorithm proposed in this study can effectively reduce the total power of short-packet secure communication under the IIoT and ensure secure data transmission.
