AU  - Y. Wang
T2  - 2022 International Symposium on Sensing and Instrumentation in 5G and IoT Era (ISSI)
AB  - As one of the main equipment of the terminal, the belt conveyor will have various faults in the complex working environment of the bulk cargo terminal. This paper mainly introduces a remote health monitoring method based on gated recurrent unit (GRU) network combined with mobile edge computing technology. The composition of belt conveyor is complex, and the amount of information generated by the equipment after the deployment of corresponding sensors is very large. Therefore, when using a single method based on the Internet of things to monitor its health, the huge amount of data generated needs to be analyzed, stored and transmitted, which cannot meet the conditions of real-time monitoring. These data can be processed using 5G mobile edge computing technology combined with deep learning methods. In the method mentioned in this paper, acquired spectrum coefficient (MFCC) and weighted bidirectional Feature Pyramid network (BiFPN) are used to preprocess the collected data, and then the data is transmitted to the GRU network, so that the system can learn the relevant fault state information, and finally the model can judge the fault information. Mobile Edge Computing (MEC) is the deployment of nodes between workers and the cloud and close to the data. With the help of data preprocessing methods and GRU networks, the analysis, judgment and transmission are carried out in the 5G environment. This method can monitor and judge the fault of belt conveyor in real time and efficiently, and realize the unmanned health monitoring of belt conveyor.
