AU  - W. Lv
AU  - X. Zhuo
T2  - 2025 3rd International Conference on Data Science and Information System (ICDSIS)
AB  - With the continuous deepening of industrial informatization, existing enterprise production line monitoring systems generally have problems such as incomplete data collection, insufficient real-time response, and inaccurate detail control. To solve these problems, this paper introduces a solution combining embedded systems with Internet of Things technology. By deploying multiple types of sensors such as temperature, humidity, pressure, vibration, and photoelectricity in key links of the production line, a real-time data collection network is built. The embedded data processing unit is used to filter, format convert, and detect anomalies on the edge layer of the raw data to achieve data preprocessing and preliminary intelligent analysis. And with the help of communication protocols such as MQTT (Message Queuing Telemetry Transport) and HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol), the processed data is transmitted to the cloud database for long-term storage and big data analysis. Through multi-channel real-time monitoring and remote control on PC (Personal Computer), Web platform, and mobile terminal, the system has achieved significant improvements in detail control. The experimental results show that in terms of data preprocessing time, the processing time of all test numbers is kept between 80ms and 110ms. In terms of packet loss rate, the packet loss rate of all tests is low, with the highest being 3% (test number 2) and the lowest being 1% (test number 3), indicating that the system has good wireless transmission stability.
