TI  - NaviGate App: A Digital Catalyst Supporting Coordination in a Smart Port Ecosystem
AU  - J. Basulo-Ribeiro
AU  - R. Gil-Pereira
AU  - B. Macedo
AU  - E. Dias
AU  - L. Teixeira
T2  - IEEE Access
AB  - The increasing complexity of port logistics and the growing need for coordinated data-driven operations have highlighted the importance of integrating truck drivers into digital transformation initiatives. This study presents the development and validation of NaviGate, a mobile application designed to improve communication, planning and operational synchronisation between truck drivers, transport companies and a Portuguese port (aiming to be a Smart Port). This paper reports the design and validation of a NaviGate prototype (interface, interaction flows and functional logic), which is being designed to support driver interaction with the future smart gate that is currently proposed for development. Using a user-centred design methodology, requirements were gathered through interviews with transport companies and questionnaires administered to drivers, forming the basis for a prototype that was subsequently validated by terminal managers and port authorities. Results indicate that drivers express a strong interest in adopting a mobile solution, recognising the need for reliable real-time information, better coordination and reduced operational uncertainty. The developed prototype integrates scheduling, real-time notifications, Guidance (process-oriented operational navigation) inside the terminal, continuous GPS-based monitoring, safety information, feedback mechanisms and a 24/7 chatbot. Theoretically, the study contributes to the conceptualisation of ports as socio-technical digital ecosystems, reinforcing evidence that digital maturity depends not only on technological infrastructures but also on the integration and acceptance of human actors, particularly truck drivers in this case, who are often overlooked in strategic planning. By demonstrating how mobile applications can operationalise this alignment, the research advances discussions on user-centred innovation in port digital transformation and supports emerging literature on collaborative smart gate ecosystems. Practically, NaviGate establishes a replicable model for ports seeking to enhance transparency, safety and efficiency through integrated, user-oriented mobile solutions. By aligning people, processes and technology, the application illustrates how digital platforms can strengthen coordination and operational resilience across port ecosystems.
