TI  - A trajectory planning algorithm for a MAV patroller in presence of wind
AU  - V. A. Nardi
T2  - 2024 IEEE International Workshop on Technologies for Defense and Security (TechDefense)
AB  - This work proposes a solution for the trajectory planning of a micro aerial vehicle (MAV) for patrolling of a cluttered outdoor scenario. Such scenarios are characterized by the presence of unpredictable wind gusts whose effects may hamper the effectiveness of MAV trajectory following. Furthermore, patrolling requires to impose constraints upon tracking error which would, otherwise, reduce both temporal and spatial resolution. By applyinga solution used in trajectory planning for skid-steer tracked vehicles, this work presents an algorithm for the planning of a trajectory which can be tracked by the MAV without violating both actuation and state constraints, even in presence of unknown but bounded external disturbance caused by the presence of wind gusts. The effectiveness of the proposed approach is shown through numerical simulations taking into account a real-world scenario of patrolling in the quay of a seaport.
