TI  - Development of Safety Risk Control System Based on Smart Safety Helmet for Oil and Gas Production
AU  - L. Ma
AU  - C. Du
AU  - H. Zhao
AU  - W. Kang
T2  - 2025 11th International Symposium on Sensors, Mechatronics and Automation System (ISSMAS)
AB  - This paper proposes a safety risk control system solution based on smart safety helmets for high-risk working environments in oil and gas production processes, including falls from heights, object strikes, and pipeline leakage. The system adopts a four-layer architecture of “edge-terminal-cloud-user” and integrates multimodal sensor arrays, BeiDou and UWB fusion positioning systems, and edge computing modules in safety helmets to achieve real-time positioning, behavior recognition, and environmental monitoring of operators. The system deploys an LSTM-based risk prediction model and multi-source data fusion platform in the cloud, effectively solving technical challenges such as strong electromagnetic interference and heterogeneous data in oil and gas production environments. Pilot application in an oilfield demonstrates that the system can reduce accident response time by 70%, with a violation operation recognition accuracy of 92.3%. It has important practical value for personnel safety assurance, environmental risk early warning, and emergency response in oil and gas production sites, providing a new technical path for intelligent safety management and control in oilfield production.
