TY  - CONF
TI  - An Energy-Health-Quality Synergetic Management Framework for Pneumatic Systems Based on Exergy and Machine Learning
AU  - Z. Wang
AU  - W. Xiong
T2  - 2023 9th International Conference on Fluid Power and Mechatronics (FPM)
AB  - Pneumatic systems are widely used in industrial production sectors. Following the evolutionary manufacturing paradigms, pneumatic technology is also moving toward the direction of digitalization, networking, intelligence, and sustainability. However, the pace is lagging behind the hydraulic and electric counterparts. Under the increasing pressure from Intelligent Manufacturing and Green Manufacturing, the drawbacks of pneumatic power in terms of energy performance and intelligence are being highlighted, and the competitiveness is challenged. Generally, energy management, prognostic and health management, and quality management are implemented independently in pneumatic systems. Here we propose an energy-health-quality synergetic management framework for pneumatic systems. The framework is exergy-centered and takes machine learning as the tool. Exergy is adopted for evaluating the available energy of compressed air. In this paper, the background and motivation are introduced first. And then the fundamental principle and the basic structure of the proposed energy-health-quality synergetic management framework are analyzed. A typical pneumatic system is taken as a case to preliminarily prove the feasibility of energy-health synergetic management. Various exergy-data-driven machine learning models are effectively tested for fault detection and diagnosis. Finally, the challenges and perspectives of implementing the proposed energy-health-quality synergetic management framework are discussed.
