TI  - Simulation and Analysis of Vision-Based Welding Operations of Micro Panels in Shipbuilding
AU  - F. Reuter
AU  - F. Casser
AU  - M. Schluse
AU  - C. Schlette
T2  - 2025 13th International Conference on Control, Mechatronics and Automation (ICCMA)
AB  - The shrinking of workforces in much of the western world calls for increased and improved automation to ensure the competitiveness of its industries. To advance the automation state in shipbuilding, this work investigates a novel approach to welding robot programming for micro panels. These basic building blocks of shipbuilding are usually welded by specialized robotic gantries using either CAD-based or vision-based programming.To combine their advantages, this work proposes and investigates a synthesis of both. A novel programming workflow is created by simulating a vision-based welding process on the Digital Model of a micro panel welding gantry. This allows for the evaluation of ship models before production begins, leading to a more reliable yet flexible production workflow.A fully automatized simulated process has been developed as groundwork for a Digital Twin, already both providing automatic analysis of the robot programs and exporting process data for manual assessment. Thus it enables a well-founded estimation of manufacturability before production begins.
